President Cyril Ramaphosa announced his much-anticipated cabinet on Wednesday and ANC secretary-general Ace Magashule commented on the decisions. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule said there were thorough collective consultations leading up to President Cyril Ramaphosa's much-anticipated cabinet announcement on Wednesday. "Well I am happy because there was thorough consultation, we engaged with the president, we engaged with the alliance and we arrived collectively where we are", said Magashule. WATCH: President Ramaphosa announces his cabinet Magashule notes that the significant rise in the number of young people added to the cabinet is important as the older generation will help to nurture them. "I think it was time for other comrades to be redeployed because we need them in other deployments to further strengthen the African National Congress and strengthen <the> government."